Singer Abbey Toyyib Elias, aka Skiibii has been thrown aback after over N2.4m electricity bill was slammed on his Lekki residence in Lagos.   Peter Olayinka dedicates match victory to new baby     Offset hints on collaboration with Burna Boy     Brillsta drops video, audio for new single ‘One…   The disgruntled “Trenches” singer challenged the Eko Electricity Distribution Company (EKEDC) for slamming him with such an outrageous sum for the previous month. He shared a photo of the electricity bill from the Lekki Business Unit which displayed the month July 2022 and the amount, N2,419,108.12. Captioning the post, a totally dazed Skiibii wrote: “What type of playing is this?”